1
00:00:20,730 --> 00:00:22,530
A strong heart along with deduction and power.

2
00:00:22,530 --> 00:00:24,230
And step into the essence with a strong rhythm.

3
00:00:24,230 --> 00:00:26,030
A beautiful and mysterious lady makes an appearance in today's episode.

4
00:00:26,030 --> 00:00:28,030
An odd request is the entrance to the case.

5
00:00:28,030 --> 00:00:29,430
He sees through the one and only truth.

6
00:00:29,430 --> 00:00:31,030
A child in appearance with the I.Q. of an adult.

7
00:00:31,030 --> 00:00:33,430
His name is Detective Conan!

8
00:01:57,810 --> 00:02:03,310
"A Client Full of Lies (Part 1)"

9
00:02:03,310 --> 00:02:06,810
"Mouri Detective Agency"

10
00:02:08,410 --> 00:02:10,510
You say, you're looking for someone?

11
00:02:10,510 --> 00:02:13,510
Yes. There is a person that I really want to see.

12
00:02:13,510 --> 00:02:17,110
Well, I'm so sorry, but I happen to be tied up just now.

13
00:02:17,110 --> 00:02:19,810
Please, will you help me, please?

14
00:02:19,810 --> 00:02:23,310
To tell you the truth, I'm right near your office already.

15
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:24,410
If it's okay with you,

16
00:02:24,410 --> 00:02:26,810
I'd like to at least be given a chance to talk to you.

17
00:02:26,810 --> 00:02:30,610
The winner is, Kaminari-Boy!

18
00:02:30,610 --> 00:02:33,010
He has won the final race with his graceful legs!

19
00:02:33,010 --> 00:02:36,110
Oh no... I lost again.

20
00:02:36,110 --> 00:02:38,110
Hello, Mr. Mouri?

21
00:02:38,110 --> 00:02:39,810
Didn't I already tell you that today I'm...

22
00:02:44,010 --> 00:02:47,210
Yes, I guess it won't hurt to hear you out.

23
00:02:47,210 --> 00:02:49,010
I'll be waiting for you.

24
00:02:51,210 --> 00:02:53,510
Come on, do your job.

25
00:02:53,510 --> 00:02:54,810
Dad!

26
00:02:54,810 --> 00:02:57,310
I know.

27
00:02:57,310 --> 00:03:00,610
What kind of person was the caller?

28
00:03:00,610 --> 00:03:02,410
Some middle aged lady.

29
00:03:02,410 --> 00:03:04,510
She says she's coming over right now.

30
00:03:04,510 --> 00:03:06,710
I'll bet she is one of those,

31
00:03:06,710 --> 00:03:11,110
"Please, please help me find my first love," type client anyway.

32
00:03:11,110 --> 00:03:13,610
I just know it.

33
00:03:15,910 --> 00:03:17,110
Please come in!

34
00:03:25,310 --> 00:03:28,410
I called just a while ago. My name is Ikenami.

35
00:03:28,410 --> 00:03:31,910
Please forgive me for intruding on you so suddenly like this.

36
00:03:31,910 --> 00:03:35,510
"Shizuka Ikenami" -An acquaintance of mine mentioned that you, Mr. Mouri

37
00:03:35,510 --> 00:03:38,210
"Client" -would definitely find the person that I'm looking for.

38
00:03:38,210 --> 00:03:40,210
Please help me.

39
00:03:40,210 --> 00:03:42,110
Please come this way.

40
00:03:42,110 --> 00:03:44,410
Talk about beautiful.

41
00:03:46,710 --> 00:03:48,110
I'm sorry.

42
00:03:48,110 --> 00:03:50,910
Where did dad go?

43
00:03:53,410 --> 00:03:57,810
I'm sorry to have kept you waiting, mademoiselle.

44
00:03:59,810 --> 00:04:05,110
I was looking through some papers of a very difficult case, you see.

45
00:04:06,110 --> 00:04:08,910
Come now, and relax on the sofa,

46
00:04:08,910 --> 00:04:10,610
and calm that pulsating heart of yours

47
00:04:10,610 --> 00:04:13,510
before I hear you out.

48
00:04:13,510 --> 00:04:16,410
Ran. Get us something to drink.

49
00:04:16,410 --> 00:04:18,310
Okay.

50
00:04:18,310 --> 00:04:20,910
Here he goes again.

51
00:04:20,910 --> 00:04:23,910
"Mouri Detective Agency"

52
00:04:23,910 --> 00:04:27,210
You're looking for a Jr. High School classmate?

53
00:04:27,210 --> 00:04:30,510
Yes, we belonged to the same kendo club.

54
00:04:30,510 --> 00:04:34,810
Couldn't you find his address on the graduation list?

55
00:04:34,810 --> 00:04:37,910
He moved before graduation,

56
00:04:37,910 --> 00:04:40,010
and the space where his name is supposed to be is blank.

57
00:04:40,010 --> 00:04:43,010
He... I see...

58
00:04:43,010 --> 00:04:45,810
I've brought a picture of him back in those days with me here.

59
00:04:47,910 --> 00:04:52,410
He's the one in the center holding the winner's cup.

60
00:04:52,410 --> 00:04:54,510
His name is Shiro Shibata.

61
00:04:54,510 --> 00:04:58,210
Isn't the girl standing next to him?

62
00:04:58,210 --> 00:05:01,610
How embarrassing, but it's me.

63
00:05:01,610 --> 00:05:04,810
It's already been 30 years though.

64
00:05:04,810 --> 00:05:06,710
Thirty years ago?

65
00:05:06,710 --> 00:05:09,010
Don't tell me that you're already over 40?

66
00:05:09,010 --> 00:05:11,910
Yes, I will be 42 this year.

67
00:05:11,910 --> 00:05:15,910
But, the boy in the picture is still in 8th grade.

68
00:05:15,910 --> 00:05:19,010
Although I think he may have grown taller by now.

69
00:05:19,010 --> 00:05:22,010
Any hobbies?

70
00:05:22,010 --> 00:05:25,410
Oh, yes... I don't think he has any special hobbies though.

71
00:05:25,410 --> 00:05:27,310
No, I mean yours.

72
00:05:28,710 --> 00:05:35,110
I like knitting, and I usually knit sweaters.

73
00:05:35,110 --> 00:05:37,710
My, what a nice hobby.

74
00:05:37,710 --> 00:05:40,610
Oh, my mother's hobby is knitting too.

75
00:05:40,610 --> 00:05:41,710
My.

76
00:05:41,710 --> 00:05:44,410
I'll bet you're good at cooking too?

77
00:05:44,410 --> 00:05:47,210
No, not at all.

78
00:05:47,210 --> 00:05:50,210
See, I cut myself in three places

79
00:05:50,210 --> 00:05:51,410
when I tried to cook after a long while last night.

80
00:05:51,410 --> 00:05:53,910
Oh well, no big deal.

81
00:05:53,910 --> 00:05:56,710
Shortcomings help make a person more attractive at times.

82
00:05:56,710 --> 00:05:59,810
Right, right, just like mother.

83
00:06:01,310 --> 00:06:04,210
But I'm full of shortcomings.

84
00:06:04,210 --> 00:06:08,410
That's why I'm still single at this age.

85
00:06:08,410 --> 00:06:11,710
-What? You're single? -Yes.

86
00:06:11,710 --> 00:06:16,510
Well, to leave a beauty like you single,

87
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:19,610
the guys around you must be blind.

88
00:06:19,610 --> 00:06:22,010
Really, what a fantastic person.

89
00:06:22,010 --> 00:06:23,410
Just like mother,

90
00:06:23,410 --> 00:06:26,310
it's hard to understand the guy who doesn't give a hoot about her.

91
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:27,510
Ran.

92
00:06:30,210 --> 00:06:31,510
I'm sorry.

93
00:06:33,210 --> 00:06:35,510
What's wrong? Do you have a cold?

94
00:06:35,510 --> 00:06:39,010
Oh, no... I was born with bronchial problems.

95
00:06:39,010 --> 00:06:41,210
I'm allergic to dust.

96
00:06:41,210 --> 00:06:42,910
I'm sorry,

97
00:06:42,910 --> 00:06:45,410
it must be dusty here because we were cleaning till just a while ago.

98
00:06:45,410 --> 00:06:48,210
Let's change places then.

99
00:06:48,210 --> 00:06:50,110
I'm sorry.

100
00:06:53,810 --> 00:06:55,510
"Cafe Poirot"

101
00:06:55,510 --> 00:06:57,010
Picture?

102
00:06:57,010 --> 00:06:59,910
So, you're looking for this Mr. Shibata

103
00:06:59,910 --> 00:07:03,210
because you want to get a picture back from him?

104
00:07:03,210 --> 00:07:04,310
Yes.

105
00:07:04,310 --> 00:07:05,710
It's only one picture that was taken

106
00:07:05,710 --> 00:07:09,410
when we won the semi-finals in a summer contest

107
00:07:09,410 --> 00:07:12,410
during our Jr. High School days.

108
00:07:12,410 --> 00:07:13,610
Just the other day,

109
00:07:13,610 --> 00:07:15,810
my grandmother seems to have mistakenly thrown away

110
00:07:15,810 --> 00:07:18,010
the plate we received then.

111
00:07:18,010 --> 00:07:21,410
So, I thought that I'd like to at least have a picture of it.

112
00:07:21,410 --> 00:07:25,110
But, why does Mr. Shibata have that picture?

113
00:07:25,110 --> 00:07:26,810
I was using that picture

114
00:07:26,810 --> 00:07:29,110
as a bookmarker for a book that I borrowed from him,

115
00:07:29,110 --> 00:07:32,510
but I forgot to take the picture out of the book when I returned it to him.

116
00:07:32,510 --> 00:07:36,910
Then, Mr. Shibata is not your first love or anything like that?

117
00:07:38,410 --> 00:07:40,710
No... well...

118
00:07:40,710 --> 00:07:44,510
And, do you have any other clues on him?

119
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:46,310
Well...

120
00:07:46,310 --> 00:07:48,010
Mr. Mouri, may I take your order?

121
00:07:48,010 --> 00:07:50,210
Coffee for me.

122
00:07:50,210 --> 00:07:51,810
I'll have iced lemon tea.

123
00:07:51,810 --> 00:07:53,310
I...

124
00:07:53,310 --> 00:07:54,410
Reiko.

125
00:07:55,510 --> 00:07:58,110
Reiko? Who is she?

126
00:07:58,110 --> 00:08:02,710
Oh no... he used to call me by that name.

127
00:08:02,710 --> 00:08:05,910
Something about the character called Reiko,

128
00:08:05,910 --> 00:08:10,410
in the book that I borrowed from him resembled me.

129
00:08:10,410 --> 00:08:12,410
What would you like, Conan?

130
00:08:12,410 --> 00:08:13,910
Ice coffee for me.

131
00:08:13,910 --> 00:08:16,010
I'll take the same.

132
00:08:16,010 --> 00:08:17,310
All right.

133
00:08:18,310 --> 00:08:21,610
So, where should I start.

134
00:08:21,610 --> 00:08:24,010
The only clues I have are his name,

135
00:08:24,010 --> 00:08:28,210
age and this picture of 30 years ago.

136
00:08:28,210 --> 00:08:35,010
-You know what... -Then, what about asking him for help?

137
00:08:35,010 --> 00:08:36,110
Him?

138
00:08:37,410 --> 00:08:39,710
I've heard rumors about him.

139
00:08:39,710 --> 00:08:41,710
Also that the high school detective,

140
00:08:41,710 --> 00:08:46,710
Shinichi Kudo is in and out of your office at times.

141
00:08:48,710 --> 00:08:50,210
Shinichi?

142
00:08:50,210 --> 00:08:53,010
Isn't that right, son?

143
00:08:53,010 --> 00:08:55,610
No, he hasn't come around at all that brat.

144
00:08:55,610 --> 00:08:58,910
He only rings me up once in a while to say stupid things.

145
00:08:58,910 --> 00:09:02,210
Well, I'm sorry that I only have stupid things to say.

146
00:09:02,210 --> 00:09:04,210
What a bummer

147
00:09:04,210 --> 00:09:06,510
to have such rumors going around.

148
00:09:08,110 --> 00:09:11,410
If worse comes to worse, they may hear about it too.

149
00:09:13,010 --> 00:09:16,110
I'll have to keep my deductions to myself for a while, I guess...

150
00:09:17,110 --> 00:09:19,210
Conan.

151
00:09:19,210 --> 00:09:21,310
What do you think, Conan?

152
00:09:22,510 --> 00:09:24,810
Well, you were about to say something just now, weren't you?

153
00:09:24,810 --> 00:09:27,910
What good is it going to do, asking a brat?

154
00:09:27,910 --> 00:09:31,810
But, he always takes note of interesting things, doesn't he?

155
00:09:31,810 --> 00:09:33,010
Oh, no, it's nothing.

156
00:09:33,010 --> 00:09:35,810
Something just happened to cross my mind.

157
00:09:35,810 --> 00:09:38,910
Since he's holding the trophy,

158
00:09:38,910 --> 00:09:41,210
this man won the tournament, right?

159
00:09:41,210 --> 00:09:42,310
Yes.

160
00:09:42,310 --> 00:09:44,110
If he was that strong when he was in the 8th grade,

161
00:09:44,110 --> 00:09:45,810
I just thought even now...

162
00:09:45,810 --> 00:09:50,110
he must be participating in some tournament.

163
00:09:52,710 --> 00:09:54,810
Oh, but I just thought maybe...

164
00:09:57,210 --> 00:09:59,410
What? He's participating?

165
00:09:59,910 --> 00:10:01,110
In the Shizuoka Tournament,

166
00:10:01,110 --> 00:10:03,710
among the general contestants, Mr. Shiro Shibata?

167
00:10:03,710 --> 00:10:06,810
Yes. Yes!

168
00:10:06,810 --> 00:10:09,510
Did you find him?

169
00:10:09,510 --> 00:10:14,010
Yeah. He seems to be a regular who always appears in the top ranks.

170
00:10:14,010 --> 00:10:18,110
He seems to be working as a high school P.E. teacher in Shizuoka.

171
00:10:18,110 --> 00:10:22,410
And is presently residing with his wife in a condominium.

172
00:10:22,410 --> 00:10:25,510
I'll go rent a car right now.

173
00:10:26,510 --> 00:10:28,810
I'm glad you found him.

174
00:10:28,810 --> 00:10:30,710
Yes, really.

175
00:10:31,910 --> 00:10:34,110
He's been found.

176
00:10:34,110 --> 00:10:37,610
The one she's looking for has been found, but...

177
00:10:37,610 --> 00:10:42,210
what I can't make out is this lady who is full of lies.

178
00:10:43,410 --> 00:10:46,310
Almost everything she says is a lie.

179
00:10:47,610 --> 00:10:49,710
I wonder what she is up to.

180
00:10:51,910 --> 00:10:56,010
Could it be that she's hiding her identity?

181
00:10:56,010 --> 00:10:57,810
Hey, hey, come on.

182
00:10:57,810 --> 00:10:59,410
Don't tell me that this lady is...

183
00:11:01,410 --> 00:11:04,810
Thank you. It's all thanks to you.

184
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:18,510
"Shibata"

185
00:11:18,510 --> 00:11:19,910
Nobody seems to be home.

186
00:11:19,910 --> 00:11:23,010
I'm sure the couple has gone out together,

187
00:11:23,010 --> 00:11:24,910
because today is Sunday.

188
00:11:24,910 --> 00:11:29,110
Why don't we go kill time somewhere nearby, then?

189
00:11:29,110 --> 00:11:30,210
Wait.

190
00:11:31,210 --> 00:11:33,110
"Takezo Yoshikawa (47)" -Are you by chance...

191
00:11:33,110 --> 00:11:35,210
"Shiro Shibata's friend" -looking for Mr. Shibata?

192
00:11:35,210 --> 00:11:37,210
Yes, sort of.

193
00:11:38,410 --> 00:11:40,810
Please finish what you have to do as soon as possible,

194
00:11:40,810 --> 00:11:44,710
because he promised to play mahjong together today at my house.

195
00:11:44,710 --> 00:11:47,210
But he doesn't seem to be in.

196
00:11:47,210 --> 00:11:49,310
It can't be.

197
00:11:49,310 --> 00:11:51,110
I'm sure he's asleep or something.

198
00:11:53,610 --> 00:11:55,510
See, he's home.

199
00:11:56,510 --> 00:11:57,810
This program is brought to you

200
00:11:57,810 --> 00:12:01,410
-by the following companies. -It's the sound of the TV.

201
00:12:01,410 --> 00:12:05,910
Come on, dozing off with the TV on without even locking the door.

202
00:12:05,910 --> 00:12:07,310
Hey, Shibata!

203
00:12:07,310 --> 00:12:09,010
We're going to start pretty soon!

204
00:12:12,710 --> 00:12:15,910
Hey, hey, it looks like he was still eating?

205
00:12:17,510 --> 00:12:21,110
The soup is cold...

206
00:12:21,110 --> 00:12:22,610
