207
00:12:22,610 --> 00:12:23,810
This couldn't be his breakfast.

208
00:12:23,810 --> 00:12:26,810
What a waste, the "guji" looks so good.

209
00:12:26,810 --> 00:12:28,610
Guji?

210
00:12:28,610 --> 00:12:30,410
I mean tilefish.

211
00:12:33,510 --> 00:12:36,010
I'm back. Dear?

212
00:12:38,610 --> 00:12:41,510
Hey, who are all of you?

213
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:44,210
"Kyoko Shibara (38), Mrs. Shibata" -Why are you in my house?

214
00:12:44,210 --> 00:12:46,210
I'm going to call the police.

215
00:12:46,210 --> 00:12:48,510
-Well, you see... -We are...

216
00:12:48,510 --> 00:12:51,310
Hey, Shibata? What's the matter?

217
00:12:51,310 --> 00:12:52,710
Get a hold of yourself. Hey.

218
00:12:52,710 --> 00:12:54,410
What's happened to you?

219
00:12:54,410 --> 00:12:57,110
Mr. Shibata!

220
00:12:57,110 --> 00:13:00,010
Mr. Shibata, get a hold of yourself.

221
00:13:01,310 --> 00:13:02,910
Mr. Shibata!

222
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:07,810
He is holding something in his right hand?

223
00:13:07,810 --> 00:13:09,210
What is it?

224
00:13:14,010 --> 00:13:16,310
This is...

225
00:13:25,020 --> 00:13:27,220
So, let me verify what you said.

226
00:13:27,220 --> 00:13:31,420
Mr. Mouri and his party came over to Mr. Shibata's house

227
00:13:31,420 --> 00:13:33,920
and pushed the button of the interphone,

228
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:35,820
but there was no answer.

229
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:41,020
Just then, Mr. Yoshikawa who had a previous engagement with came along

230
00:13:41,020 --> 00:13:42,520
and tried turning the knob of the door.

231
00:13:42,520 --> 00:13:45,120
The door was unlocked,

232
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:48,520
so the five of you came into the room.

233
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:51,720
Then, Mrs. Shibata, Mr. Shibata's wife,

234
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:53,620
who had been out comes back

235
00:13:53,620 --> 00:13:55,920
and runs into Mr. Mouri and the others.

236
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:59,020
After that, upon hearing Mr. Yoshikawa shout,

237
00:13:59,020 --> 00:14:01,520
you all go to the living room to check things out

238
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:06,920
and found Mr. Shibata bleeding from the head and dead.

239
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:08,420
Yeah.

240
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:14,320
The estimated time of death is between dawn and morning today.

241
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:16,420
All right.

242
00:14:16,420 --> 00:14:19,120
Where were you around that time, Mrs. Shibata?

243
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:20,220
Yes.

244
00:14:20,220 --> 00:14:23,520
I had a golf date with a friend of mine today,

245
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:27,620
and my friend came to pick me up.

246
00:14:27,620 --> 00:14:30,520
So, I prepared my husband's lunch,

247
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:32,820
and left the house before 05:00 am.

248
00:14:34,220 --> 00:14:37,720
Was Mr. Shibata at home then?

249
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:42,620
Yes, he came home about 03:00 am and was fast asleep.

250
00:14:42,620 --> 00:14:45,020
He came home at 03:00 am?

251
00:14:45,020 --> 00:14:46,220
Yes.

252
00:14:46,220 --> 00:14:48,020
We were playing mahjong.

253
00:14:48,020 --> 00:14:50,020
We were playing mahjong at my room

254
00:14:50,020 --> 00:14:51,720
that is on the fourth floor.

255
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:53,120
Just as Mrs. Shibata says,

256
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:55,620
we finished the game around 03:00 am.

257
00:14:56,720 --> 00:15:00,620
As a matter of fact, the morning paper was one the table,

258
00:15:00,620 --> 00:15:03,420
about what time is the newspaper delivered?

259
00:15:03,420 --> 00:15:06,420
It comes about 06:00 am

260
00:15:06,420 --> 00:15:08,620
and is put inside the mailbox right outside the front door.

261
00:15:08,620 --> 00:15:11,820
I see, which means that Mr. Shibata,

262
00:15:11,820 --> 00:15:13,720
got up in the morning,

263
